      "content": "Here's a draft rejection email that's both professional and kind:\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer role at [Company Name]. We were truly impressed by your exceptional system design skills and your alignment with our company culture. However, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience with our specific cloud stack aligns more closely with our current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely excited about the prospect of having you join our team. Your passion for system design and your ability to think critically are truly impressive, and we have no doubt that you will go on to achieve great things in your career.\n\nWe appreciate the time and effort you invested in our interview process, and we're grateful for the opportunity to have met you. We wish you all the best in your job search and hope that our paths will cross again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nI hope this draft meets your requirements. You know, just like a skilled engineer, a good rejection email should be well-structured, clear, and concise, while also leaving a positive impression.",
